Going nine hours.

9
00:00:26,010 --> 00:00:27,490
Leonard Steinberg -

10
00:00:27,510 --> 00:00:29,390
He checked in this morning
for a hernia operation.

11
00:00:29,410 --> 00:00:32,090
Nine hours? Food, water?
A bathroom break?

12
00:00:32,110 --> 00:00:33,990
Just stands there on the edge,
looking down,

13
00:00:34,010 --> 00:00:35,890
Threatening to jump
if anyone comes close.

14
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:36,900
Uh-Huh.

15
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,290
Police negotiator's
getting so frustrated

16
00:00:39,310 --> 00:00:42,090
He's about to
push him off himself.

17
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:44,390
I called you hoping
for a little magic.

18
00:00:44,410 --> 00:00:46,600
Nine hours. Tommy!

19
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:47,790
Yes, Dr. Gallagher?

20
00:00:47,810 --> 00:00:48,790
Do me a favor,
will you?

21
00:00:48,810 --> 00:00:50,990
Call Mort's deli for me
and order, uh -

22
00:00:51,010 --> 00:00:53,390
Order a sky-high pastrami
sandwich, lean, on rye,

23
00:00:53,410 --> 00:00:55,490
With some new pickles,
and rush the delivery.

24
00:00:55,510 --> 00:00:57,000
Wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait!

25
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:59,990
Make that two sky-highs and
a couple of deli cream sodas.

26
00:01:00,010 --> 00:01:02,690
Money's in my desk.
Thanks, Tommy.

27
00:01:02,710 --> 00:01:05,300
There's no rush.
Plenty of time for a snack.

28
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:08,500
Hank, push the button.

29
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:15,490
You want to see me
go splat?!

30
00:01:15,510 --> 00:01:17,490
Take another step,
dumb cop!

31
00:01:17,510 --> 00:01:20,090
Mr. Steinberg, at least let us
get you some dry clothes.

32
00:01:20,110 --> 00:01:21,890
Come on, a little closer!

33
00:01:21,910 --> 00:01:24,390
See the middle-aged Jew
take his first flying lesson!

34
00:01:24,410 --> 00:01:25,690
Sir, you don't
want to do this.

35
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:28,800
You want to bet, grandpa?
I'll even give you odds!

36
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:31,990
Who's this clown?

37
00:01:32,010 --> 00:01:34,200
Gallagher, head shrink.

38
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:35,800
Wow.

39
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,700
Nice night for it.

40
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,690
You think you're gonna
talk me down.

41
00:01:40,710 --> 00:01:42,400
Wouldn't even consider it.

42
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,900
Everyone's got a right
to die, Leonard.

43
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:49,000
News choppers were here earlier
before the weather blew in.

44
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,190
Sorry I missed it.

45
00:01:51,210 --> 00:01:52,790
My family show up?

46
00:01:52,810 --> 00:01:54,100
No idea.

47
