Suckered again.

125
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,900
Ms. Crane.

126
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,800
I'm Dr. Gallagher.

127
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,490
I'm - I'm looking
for Dr. Howard.

128
00:05:51,510 --> 00:05:52,890
We have a deposition scheduled
for this morning.

129
00:05:52,910 --> 00:05:54,700
Actually, the deposition
is with me.

130
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,800
What?
I'm filling in.

131
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,500
yeah, I don't think so.

132
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:03,790
Marcie Crane. I need to speak
to judge latimer immediately.

133
00:06:03,810 --> 00:06:04,900
Yeah, I'll hold.

134
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,200
Excuse me.

135
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,090
I don't know what you and
the public defender's office

136
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:11,590
Are trying to pull, but
I'm here to depose Dr. Howard

137
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:13,390
Regarding his memorandum
to the court in the matter of -

138
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:16,400
Trey Hansen, charged
with first-degree murder.

139
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:19,090
I wrote the memorandum,
not Dr. Howard.

140
00:06:19,110 --> 00:06:19,990
You did?

141
00:06:20,010 --> 00:06:21,100
Yes, ma'am.

142
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:24,000
I assumed
you'd read my report.

143
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,990
Uh, of course
I read it.

144
00:06:27,010 --> 00:06:28,790
Great. You're
the court reporter?

145
00:06:28,810 --> 00:06:30,300
Yes, I am.

146
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,000
You ladies
like to follow me?

147
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,800
I'm sorry
for all the confusion.

148
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,390
Dr. Howard
was originally retained

149
00:06:36,410 --> 00:06:38,990
By the public defender's office,
but he became unavailable.

150
00:06:39,010 --> 00:06:39,990
So I stepped in.

151
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:41,690
Mr. Hansen
is a patient of yours?

152
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:42,990
Yes, yes, he is.

153
00:06:43,010 --> 00:06:45,100
He's currently undergoing
treatment for his condition.

154
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:46,790
I'm sure he is.

155
00:06:46,810 --> 00:06:48,790
This is some kind of crusade
for you, isn't it, doctor -

156
00:06:48,810 --> 00:06:51,190
Save the innocent patient
from the clutches of the law?

157
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:52,790
Prosecutor or not,
Ms. Crane,

158
00:06:52,810 --> 00:06:54,490
Shouldn't this be a crusade
for you, too,

159
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:56,600
as a representative
of the state?

160
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:58,490
Except that
your innocent patient

161
00:06:58,510 --> 00:06:59,900
murdered another
human being.

162
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:01,300
Allegedly.

163
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,890
Marcie, Lynn Conivar,
PD.'s office.

164
00:07:05,910 --> 00:07:07,500
We've met at several
bar functions.

165
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:10,700
Of course, Lynn.
Nice to see you again.

166
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,500
You don't remember me,
do you?

167
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,500
Sorry. No.

168
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,190
If I could have a moment

169
00:07:20,210 --> 00:07:22,090
To review Dr. Gallagher's
memorandum?

170
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:23,300
No problem.

171
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,800
Can I offer anyone
anything to drink?

172
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,090
Tea? Coffee?
Pint of blood?

173
00:07:31,110 --> 00:07:32,090
No, thank you.

174
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:33,500
I'm fine.

175
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:37,890
I, um, think
we're ready.

176
00:07:37,910 --> 00:07:38,690
No objection.

177
00:07:38,710 --> 00:07:39,990
I'd like to state first,
for the record,

178
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:41,390
That this deposition
is being held

179
00:07:41,410 --> 00:07:42,390
At wharton memorial hospital

180
00:07:42,410 --> 00:07:44,600
Per the defense and
so ordered by the court.

181
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,200
Noted.

182
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:50,590
Dr. Gallagher, when is the first
time you met Trey Hansen?

183
00:07:50,610 --> 00:07:51,590
15 days ago.

184
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:54,800
So, approximately nine months
after the murder of Andrew Wohl?

185
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:55,790
That's correct.

186
00:07:55,810 --> 00:07:57,790
In general, is nine months
sufficient time

187
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,890
For a psychiatric patient's
mental state

188
00:07:59,910 --> 00:08:01,690
To change significantly,
for better or worse?

189
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:02,790
In general, yes.

190
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:04,990
So, the memorandum
that you prepared

191
00:08:05,010 --> 00:08:08,190
describes Trey Hansen's
current mental state,

192
00:08:08,210 --> 00:08:10,290
rather than any mental state that may
or may not have existed

193
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:11,390
on the day
the crime occurred.

194
00:08:11,410 --> 00:08:13,290
Certain characteristics
wouldn't have changed.

195
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:15,690
Yes-or-No question,
doctor. It's "yes" and "no. "

196
00:08:15,710 --> 00:08:18,290
Meaning that your report
may or may not be valid.

197
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:18,990
Objection.

198
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:21,300
Dr. Gallagher, what is
Trey Hansen's I.Q.?

199
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,490
I didn't conduct
those tests.

200
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:25,700
But you're familiar
with the results.

201
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:27,090
It's around 75.

202
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:29,090
Low.
Below average.

203
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:32,700
Is Trey Hansen capable of
distinguishing right from wrong?

204
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,190
Yes.

205
00:08:34,210 --> 00:08:35,690
Is he capable
of understanding

206
00:08:35,710 --> 00:08:38,890
The consequences of his actions,
cause and effect -

207
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:42,090
For example, the cause of
his running a sharp knife

208
00:08:42,110 --> 00:08:43,290
across the throat
of Andrew Wohl

209
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:44,490
And the effect of Mr. Wohl

210
00:08:44,510 --> 00:08:45,890
bleeding to death
within minutes?

211
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:46,790
Objection.

212
00:08:46,810 --> 00:08:49,000
Trey Hansen understands
cause and effect.

213
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,600
Thank you.

214
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,590
I'd like to direct
your attention now

215
00:08:53,610 --> 00:08:54,590
To paragraph two

216
00:08:54,610 --> 00:08:57,700
Of your very
imaginative report.

217
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,000
That concludes
my questions.

218
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:07,500
Well, that wasn't
too terrible.

219
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,200
It gets worse.

220
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,090
May we talk in private?

221
00:09:12,110 --> 00:09:16,100
Of course. I'd like
Dr. Gallagher to stay.

222
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,190
This is my best offer -

223
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:27,190
Voluntary manslaughter,
15 to 20,

224
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:29,100
based on the retardation.

225
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,390
My client is innocent
of any crime.

226
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:34,500
Going...

227
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:39,700
...gone.

228
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:42,200
I'll see you in court.

229
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:52,290
I can't believe it.

230
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:53,790
Did we just break through?

231
00:09:53,810 --> 00:09:55,590
Too soon to tell.

232
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:57,700
But it's definitely
a new wrinkle.

233
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,790
Anyone drop by to see him?

234
00:10:00,810 --> 00:10:02,790
I called his ex-wife and kids,
told them he was here.

235
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:04,290
No takers.
Medication?

236
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:06,600
Haldol, Ativan, Cogentin -
5, 2, 1.

237
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:07,990
That should have
calmed him down.

238
00:10:08,010 --> 00:10:09,590
Oh... he told me he knew

239
00:10:09,610 --> 00:10:10,990
how to swallow his tongue
and suffocate.

240
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:12,600
That's a myth, isn't it?

241
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:14,600
Unless he bites
it off first.

242
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,890
How do you feel about
dying today, Leonard?

243
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:20,990
Thinking about it.

244
00:10:21,010 --> 00:10:22,490
Any particular reason?

245
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,490
Well, I sure screwed up
my life pretty bad.

246
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:25,690
That's a fact.

247
00:10:25,710 --> 00:10:28,690
And then there's the 56k
as of yesterday.

248
00:10:28,710 --> 00:10:30,100
What happened yesterday?

249
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,890
No way the Cubs
lose that game!

250
00:10:31,910 --> 00:10:35,390
Garza on the mound, Robinson
on a 16-game hitting streak,

251
00:10:35,410 --> 00:10:37,390
St. Louis in the cellar -
No way!

252
00:10:37,410 --> 00:10:39,490
Throwing error in the 9th.
Two runs scored.

253
00:10:39,510 --> 00:10:41,790
Just my stinking,
rotten luck.

254
00:10:41,810 --> 00:10:43,100
Wait a second.

255
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,290
You bet 56k
on a baseball game?

256
00:10:46,310 --> 00:10:47,590
25.

257
00:10:47,610 --> 00:10:48,990
Would have put me square
with Jimmy

258
00:10:49,010 --> 00:10:50,990
And paid for
the hernia operation.

259
00:10:51,010 --> 00:10:52,390
Now I'm dead meat.

260
00:10:52,410 --> 00:10:53,700
Jimmy's your bookie?

261
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:56,290
He does this thing
with a ball peen hammer.

262
